		.story-block
			header.story-block-header
				h2 03-05/2014 &mdash; Behance Portfolio Reviews
				h4 Organizer

			.story-block-body
				p I was the lead organizer of #[a(href='http://www.geekvillelearning.it/offerta-formativa/behance-portfolio-review-verona/', target='_blank') Behance Portfolio Reviews Verona 2014,] for the first time ever in the city.

				p Behance Portfolio Review is a networking event aimed specifically at creatives, with the purpose of promoting the practice of design critique.

				p As an organizer, I took care of:

				ul
					li Marketing the event;
					li Selling tickets;
					li Preparing the event location (before &amp; after the event);
					li Running the event;
					li Communicating with Behance HQ in US.

				p Credits: a big help for recruiting Special Guests and Review Leaders came from Stefano Torregrossa &amp; Matteo Cuccato, who leveraged their personal and professional network for the cause.

		.story-block
			header.story-block-header
				h2 04/2013 &mdash; Startup Weekend
				h4 Coach

			.story-block-body
				p In april 2013, #[a(href='https://web.archive.org/web/20131115072955/http://venice.startupweekend.org/', target='_blank') H-Farm](http://www.h-farmventures.com/en/) (one of the top italian startup accelerators) organized and hosted [Startup Weekend Venice 2013;] I was invited to join the event as a Coach.

				p The role of Coaches in Startup Weekend's formula is an important one: a Coach is basically an expert in his field &mdash; in my case, UI Design &amp; Logo Design &mdash; who follows each team and contributes with his knowledge.

		.story-block
			header.story-block-header
				h2 10-12/2012 &mdash; Startup Weekend
				h4 Organizer

			.story-block-body
				p I was one of the 3-people-team who organized #[a(href='https://web.archive.org/web/20121217072032/http://verona.startupweekend.org/', target='_blank') Startup Weekend Verona 2012,] for the first time ever in the city.

				p Organizing a Startup Weekend is no easy task: it involves a lot of planning and the ability to wear many different hats:

				ol
					li Finding sponsors;
					li Recruiting Coaches and Jury members;
					li Marketing the event;
					li Doing PR for the event;
					li Selling tickets and providing customer service;
					li Preparing the event location (before &amp; after the event);
					li Running the event, &amp; making sure it follows the planned schedule;
					li Assigning prizes, and communicating with the sponsors who make them available;
					li Doing admin work (collecting payments, invoicing, etc);
					li Constantly communicating with Startup Weekend HQ in US.

				p I worked mostly in areas 02, 03, 05, 06, 08.

				p I also created the event identity: #[a(href='http://www.simplest.io/work/startup-weekend-verona.html?ref=dtc-resume', target='_blank') &rarr; Startup Weekend Verona 2012 on Simplest]

				p Thanks to the work of everyone involved the event was a success, with 120+ attendees.
